          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "LEAST",
                "INTAD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The Cook least-square method for  (g,p)",
                " reaction  differential  cross section obtaining from",
                " (e,e'p) reaction cross sections measured  using  the",
                " direct   proton   detection   with   the   following",
                " integration over angles."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Root-mean-squared errors."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The cross sections of the (e,e'p) reaction  on  44Ca,",
                " 45Sc and  46Ti have been measured and used to deduce",
                " (g,p) cross  sections.  Together  with  (g,n)  cross",
                " sections from  others,  these data allow to estimate",
                " of  the  T<  and   T>   GDR   cross   sections.  The",
                " experimental results  seem to be consistent with the",
                " theory on the  isospin  splitting.  The  (g,p-0)  or",
                " (g,(p-0)+(p-1)) and (g,a-0) cross sections have been",
                " also been measured.  The  ratio  sig(g,p-0)/sig(g,p)",
                " indicates  a contribution of a statistical nature in",
                " the T> gdr region and some additional  direct  modes",
                " in the T> GDR region. The contribution of one (45Sc)",
                " or two (46Ti) extra protons is discussed and  it  is",
                " found that the valence nucleons contribute to GDR in",
                " an independent way."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "STATUS": [
